WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:04.600 --> 00:00:09.400
The OtterBox Defender Series offers all
around rugged protection.

00:00:09.400 --> 00:00:14.000
To install your device into the case, first remove
the case from the holster style belt clip.

00:00:14.000 --> 00:00:17.100
Now separate the silicone from the hard plastic shell.

00:00:17.160 --> 00:00:22.100
Be careful not to pull for any ports or plugs.

00:00:33.400 --> 00:00:44.000
You can separate the two pieces of the shell by 
releasing the tension clips along the side of the case.

00:00:49.440 --> 00:00:59.900
Now place the device into the back half of the plastic, 
making sure all the features line up.

00:01:04.460 --> 00:01:10.579
You can now snap on the front piece.

00:01:10.579 --> 00:01:21.100
We'll now place the silicon back on the
case, making sure everything seats into place.

00:01:28.250 --> 00:01:31.600
Your device is now protected.

00:01:31.600 --> 00:01:34.219
The holster is designed for the screen to face in for maximum protection

00:01:34.219 --> 00:01:38.979
however can be used face out if desired.

00:01:38.979 --> 00:01:43.200
The holster also turns into a stand for
your device. Simply pull out on the belt clip

00:01:43.240 --> 00:01:50.240
until it locks into place now rotate the
belt clip did the desired viewing angle.

00:01:56.350 --> 00:02:03.350
To release it, push up on the tab at the
top for the belt clip.

00:02:10.050 --> 00:02:12.130
There you have it, the OtterBox Defender
Series.

